                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1115/1450: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Jean de Luz</hi>
                        </placeName>,<note n="27" xml:id="d718fn27">On September 10, the Ambassador
                            notified the Department that the hotel at Hendaye was closing and that
                            he was moving the Chancery to the Hotel Miramar at St. Jean de Luz
                            (124.52/114).</note>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-12T12:00:00+01:00">September 12,
                            1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 12—9:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. The following telegram has been received from Chapman: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“What attitude should I assume in cases of American citizens towards
                            Governor’s order that no foreigner may embark for foreign destination
                            without his permission ?”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Have replied as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Until permission is refused by Governor to Americans, do nothing. In the
                            meantime call on Governor and say that you naturally assume there would
                            not be the slightest difficulty about the evacuation of American
                            citizens.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
